# Walkthrough - LinkedIn SSO & ML Optimization

We have successfully resolved the LinkedIn authentication loop and significantly optimized the performance of the ML resume parsing service.

## 1. LinkedIn SSO Resolution (3-Layered Fix)

LinkedIn's OIDC implementation is non-standard for confidential server-side applications. We implemented three specific bypasses to handle their quirks:

- **Nonce Bypass**: LinkedIn often omits the `nonce` claim in the ID Token. We created a custom `JwtDecoderFactory` to skip this strict check.
- **PKCE Removal**: LinkedIn rejects authorization codes if PKCE parameters (`code_challenge`) are sent from a confidential app. We modified [CustomOAuth2AuthorizationRequestResolver](file:///c:/Users/swarn/OneDrive/Desktop/smart-resume-backend-final/src/main/java/com/smartresume/config/CustomOAuth2AuthorizationRequestResolver.java#23-84) to strip these parameters.
- **Issuer Validation**: LinkedIn returns an `iss` claim of `https://www.linkedin.com`, which doesn't match the standard $OIDC$ `issuer-uri`. We implemented a custom validator in [SecurityConfig.java](file:///c:/Users/swarn/OneDrive/Desktop/smart-resume-backend-final/src/main/java/com/smartresume/config/SecurityConfig.java) to explicitly allow this format.

