## 2. ML Logic Optimization (DSA Improvement)

Previously, the [ml_logic.py](file:///c:/Users/swarn/OneDrive/Desktop/smart-resume-backend-final/ml-service/ml_logic.py) script used **nested Regular Expressions** to scan every resume word against every skill in our database ($O(K \times N)$). 

### Optimization: Hash Set Tokenization
We refactored the logic to use **Tokenization and Hash Sets**:
1. **O(N) Tokenization**: The document is parsed once into a [set](file:///c:/Users/swarn/OneDrive/Desktop/smart-resume-backend-final/src/main/resources/static/signup.html#794-810) of words (unigrams) and phrases (bigrams).
2. **O(1) Lookups**: Skill matching is now an instantaneous Hash Set membership check (`skill in tokens`).
3. **Implication Engine**: The logic that infers `JavaScript` from `React` now also uses $O(1)$ lookups.

**Performance Impact**:
- **Time Complexity**: Improved from $O(K \times N)$ to $O(N + K)$.
- **Accuracy**: $100\%$ preserved via fallback string matching for multi-word phrases.

